</li> <li class="nav-item "> <a class="nav-link" href="/group">group </a> </li> <li class="nav-item "> <a class="nav-link" href="/publications/">publications </a> </li> <li class="nav-item "> <a class="nav-link" href="/teaching/">teaching </a> </li> <li class="nav-item "> <a class="nav-link" href="/service/">service </a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </nav> <progress id="progress" value="0"> <div class="progress-container"> <span class="progress-bar"></span> </div> </progress> </header> <div class="container mt-5" role="main"> <div class="post"> <article> <div class="profile float-right"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/dkim-profile-2025-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/dkim-profile-2025-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/dkim-profile-2025-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="(min-width: 800px) 231.0px, (min-width: 576px) 30vw, 95vw" type="image/webp"> <script src="/cdn-cgi/scripts/7d0fa10a/cloudflare-static/rocket-loader.min.js" data-cf-settings="e84a4a28f2097eae4107b3c3-|49"></script><img src="/assets/img/dkim-profile-2025.png?44bef85fa47a2380324abc6ab18090ca" class="img-fluid z-depth-1 rounded" width="100%" height="auto" alt="dkim-profile-2025.png" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"> </source></picture> </figure> <div class="more-info"></div> </div> <div class="clearfix"> <blockquote> Assistant Professor of Computer Science<br> The University of Texas at Austin<br><p></p> <i class="fa-solid fa-building"></i> <a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/2c48uUza7ZeAXMjw9" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">GDC 6.824</a><br> <i class="fa-solid fa-envelope"></i> <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#365257535e4f53595d764342534e574518535243"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="0c686d6964756963674c797869746d7f22696879">[email&#160;protected]</span></a> | <i class="fa-brands fa-google-scholar"></i> <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=n017nRYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google Scholar</a> | <i class="fa fa-1x fa-play-circle"></i> <a href="#" onclick="if (!window.__cfRLUnblockHandlers) return false; play('name')" data-cf-modified-e84a4a28f2097eae4107b3c3-="">My first name</a><br> </blockquote> <p>I am an Assistant Professor of <a href="https://cs.utexas.edu/" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Computer Science</a> at the <a href="https://www.utexas.edu/" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">University of Texas at Austin</a>. I co-lead the <a href="https://utns.cs.utexas.edu" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">UT Networked Systems Research Group</a> and am also a member of the <a href="https://wncg.org/" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Wireless Networking and Communications Group</a> and <a href="http://6g-ut.org/" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">6G@UT</a>. I am a co-PI of the <a href="https://ldos.utexas.edu/" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">LDOS NSF Expeditions in Computing project</a>.</p> <p>My research focuses on designing new systems and abstractions for virtualized, programmable, and heterogeneous computing infrastructures to address challenges in programming, resilience, security, and runtime resource management. Current projects include:</p> <ul> <li><a href="#">Operating system for programmable network infrastructure</a></li> <li><a href="https://daehyeok.kim/projects/celledge/">Cellular network edge infrastructure for latency-critical applications</a></li> <li><a href="https://transcraft.io/" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Network infrastructure for AI and HPC applications</a></li> <li><a href="https://ldos.utexas.edu/" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Learning-baesd resource management for hetergenous computing infrastructures</a></li> </ul> <p>Prior to joining UT Austin, I was a senior researcher at <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/lab/microsoft-research-redmond/" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Microsoft Research Redmond</a>. I received my PhD from the Computer Science Department at Carnegie Mellon University, where I was advised by <a href="https://users.ece.cmu.edu/~vsekar/" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Vyas Sekar</a> and <a href="https://www.cs.cmu.edu/~srini/" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Srinivasan Seshan</a>. My <a href="https://daehyeok.kim/assets/papers/cmu-phd-thesis.pdf">dissertation</a> introduced new abstractions and runtime systems to enable elastic and resilient in-network computing. My work was supported in part by the <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/academic-program/phd-fellowship/#!fellows" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Microsoft Research PhD Fellowship</a>. Prior to joining CMU, I worked as a research scientist at KAIST. Before that, I received BS and MS degrees in Computer Science and Engineering from POSTECH, South Korea.</p> </div> </article> </div> </div> <footer class="fixed-bottom" role="contentinfo"> <div class="container mt-0"> © Copyright 2026 Daehyeok Kim. Powered by <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/" target="_blank" rel="external nofollow noopener">Jekyll</a> with <a href="https://github.com/alshedivat/al-folio" rel="external nofollow noopener" target="_blank">al-folio</a> theme. </div> </footer> <audio id="name" src="/assets/audio/daehyeok.mp3"></audio> <script data-cfasync="false" src="/cdn-cgi/scripts/5c5dd728/cloudflare-static/email-decode.min.js"></script><script type="e84a4a28f2097eae4107b3c3-text/javascript">function play(e){document.getElementById(e).play()}</script> <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/jquery@3.6.0/dist/jquery.min.js" integrity="sha256-/xUj+3OJU5yExlq6GSYGSHk7tPXikynS7ogEvDej/m4=" crossorigin="anonymous" type="e84a4a28f2097eae4107b3c3-text/javascript"></script> <script src="/assets/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" type="e84a4a28f2097eae4107b3c3-text/javascript"></script> <script s